condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :3.01 | Description :The Recipient declares its commitment Project's objective and shall carry out the Projectthrough SAG and SEFIN in accordance with t he provisions of Article IV of the General Conditions. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :3.02 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the Project is carried out in accordance with the provisionsof Schedule 2 to this Agreement. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch 2, I.A.2.a(i) | Description :The Recipient, through SAG, shall maintain throughout Project implementation, aProject coordination unit (PCU), with composition, f unctions and responsibilities acceptable to the Association. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch 2, I.A.2.b(i) | Description :The Recipient, through SEFIN, shall maintain throughout Project implementationa Project administration unit (UAP), with composition , functions and responsibilities acceptable to the Association. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch 2, I.A.2.c. | Description :PCU and UAP personnel shall only be hired based on professional criteria andshall only be replaced for reasons related to performan ce. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Sch 2, I.B.1.a | Description :The Recipient shall, through SAG and SEFIN, adopt a Project operational manualacceptable to the Association. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Sch 2, I.B.1.b | Description :The Recipient, through SAG and SEFIN, shall carry out the Project in accordancewith the Operational Manual. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Sch 2, I.C. | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the Project is carried out in accordance with theprovisions of the Anti-Corruption Guidelines. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch 2, I.D.2 | Description :The Recipient, through SAG and SEFIN, shall make a Productive Grant to the eligibleRPO under the respective Productive Grant Agreement, under procedures set forth in the Operational Manual. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Sch 2, I.D.2.c | Description :The business plans for Productive Subprojects shall be approved by an evaluationcommittee, satisfactory to the Association. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch 2, I.E.1. | Description :The Recipient, through SAG, shall ensure that the RPOs carry out the ProductiveSubprojects in accordance with the Environmental Management Plan and the IPP prepared for the Project. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch 2, I.F.1. | Description :No later than 90 days after the Effective Date, the Recipient, through SAG andSEFIN, shall select a pay agent for Component 2, acce ptable to the Association. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch 2, I.F.2. | Description :The Recipient shall maintain throughout Project implementation, a credit guaranteefund satisfactory to the Association, set up with the Recipient's own resources totaling of $5 million equivalent. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch 2, II.B.4. | Description :Within 90 days after the Effective Date, the Recipient, through SEFIN, shallcomplete the action plan, dated April 8, 2008, for thestrengthening of SEFIN#s financial management for the Project. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch. 2 Sec.I.A.1 | Description :The Recipient shall establish and maintain throughout Project implementation asteering committee responsible for Project oversightand coordination. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.E para. 1 | Description :The Recipient, through INVEST-H, shall carry out Parts 1, 2 and 3of the Project, and shall ensure that the RPOs carry out the Productive Subprojects in accordance with the ESMF, containing interalia the RPF and IPPF. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.F para. 2 | Description :The project shall maintain throughout Project implementation, acredit guarantee fund satisfactory to the Bank, in accordance with the structure and procedures set forth in the ProjectOperational Manual. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule Section I.F para. 1 | Description :The Recipient shall: (a) not later than three months after theEffective Date, hire independent auditors, acceptable to the Association, and under terms of reference acceptable to theAssociation, to carry out operational audits integrating the results of the implementation of Part 2.A of the Project; and (b) notlater than 90 days after audit, submit report to the Association. | Frequency :Yearly
